        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 12:53PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1253 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
near Big Timber, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Big Timber and Greycliff.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
